						               													<description>L&amp;rsquo;eredit&amp;agrave; recreates the atmosphere of the Italian TV quiz game by re-proposing the challenges that made it famous, in particular the final one (La ghigliottina). There isn&amp;rsquo;t a host, but all the players compete for the final victory, taking turns asking questions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The challenges are Il domino musicale, Una tira l&amp;rsquo;altra, I fantastici 4, La sfida (which takes place at the end of each of the first 3 rehearsals), Il triello, I calci di rigore and La ghigliottina.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is no elimination of players, but whoever is defeated by the challenge loses &amp;euro; 10,000. The questions are taken from the TV show and are divided into 3 levels of difficulty, so you can play at all ages: in fact, at the beginning of the game players can decide whether to play all with the same level, with a random level that changes for each question or everyone with their own level.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player wins who, among those who have guessed the guillotine word, has the highest inheritance.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
